<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1058,483,593]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1167">D i a g n o s i s: Forebody castaneous; rest testaceous, except region near elytral apex yellow and each elytron with 3 yellow markings, one faintly visible at elytral base near mesoscutellum, one positioned in front of middle near epipleural margin, one postmedial near sutural margin.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1059,609,777]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1167">
D e s c r i p t i o n: Size: Length 8.0 mm; width 2.0 mm. Form: As in 
<figureCitation box="[897,983,609,631]" captionStart="Figs 116-119" captionStartId="96.[151,191,1523,1545]" captionTargetBox="[150,1045,197,1512]" captionTargetId="figure-28@96.[150,1045,197,1512]" captionTargetPageId="96" captionText="Figs 116-119. Habitus. Priocera championi nov.sp. (116), P. catalinae (117), P. chilotaxis nov.sp. (118), P. chiricahuae (119)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5039200" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5039200/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="1167">Fig. 116</figureCitation>
. Head: Cranium wrinkled; frons wider than length of antennal pedicel (
<collectionCode box="[807,846,638,659]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1167">EW</collectionCode>
/FW 30/30). Thorax: Pronotum wrinkled, with 2 tumescenses (
<collectionCode box="[589,628,667,688]" country="Thailand" name="Paleontological Collections" pageId="22" pageNumber="1167">PW</collectionCode>
/PL 80/120); elytral disc sculptured with striate, asetiferous punctures that extend to elytral distal 3/4 
<superScript attach="left" box="[840,852,693,707]" fontSize="6" pageId="22" pageNumber="1167">th</superScript>
(
<collectionCode box="[876,907,697,718]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1167">EL</collectionCode>
/EW 350/75); metathoracic femur gradually increasing in diameter to femoral apex. Abdomen: Pygidium scutiform.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,880,793,815]" box="[151,880,793,815]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1167">
